I would NOT recommend Emma’s and will never order from them again.  I ordered two trays of food that were supposed to feed four people each for a total Of $120!  I received a loaf of Italian bread,  tray of salad, chicken pesto tray and chicken parm tray.  When I got home I noticed there was no pasta for the chicken parm.  I called to express my disappointment.  A couple minutes later I got a call back from the “manager”.....some younger “lady” with no customer service skills.  She said I should have read the menu and they don’t serve pasta with their trays.  I have ordered plenty of chicken parm in my day and it’s NEVER been served without pasta.  What she should have said is I’m sorry that wasn’t explained to you and we would be happy to give you some pasta to go with it.  I would have gladly paid for it.  What i didn’t want to do was to have to cook on xmas eve and that is why I ordered out.  I asked her why she even called me and her response was , well we aren’t wrong and you should have read the menu!  It’s not about right or wrong  and Emma’s you need to either get a new “manager” or teach this one some customer service skills!!!  As a side note, my comment was removed from your Facebook page so i wanted to post elsewhere for others to beware!

I was so excited to sink my teeth into a bountiful feast from Emma's. I heard amazing things. I got the shrimp Alfredo. $22.  When I got the meal home I opened it up and looked down at the steamy Alfredo goodness. Yet. Upon laying my eyes upon the white ocean of angel hair pasta. I saw two shrimp. Just two average sized shrimp.  Now Initially my blood boiled as hot and steamy as the wofting scent of the Alfredo feast before me. Then I looked beneath the mountain of pasta and found what I was looking for!! Shrimp!  Exactly one more shrimp. For the value price of just $22 I was able to get triplets!  Now. The food tasted ok.  But  in what backwards ridiculous word does a $2.49 box of Barilla and $2 worth of shrimp equate to $22? In Emma's of Westfield.  Note to self. Save $17.51 and make it myself next time and get a fair serving of shrimp with my shrimp Alfredo.

We went New Year's Eve and this review may not reflect Emma's true colors.  We have been there in the past and found the food to always be hot and tasty.  New Years dinner out can be hectic for restaurant owners as menu items change for the evening as was the case for Emma's.  They offered three appetizers and 5 entrees.  We were dissapointed as we came for items we had in the past and their extensive menu was drastically chopped.  However, my husband ordered scallops and I the filet, with calamari for an appetizer.  Calamari is always delicious.  Hot with plenty of sauce.  Salads were standard as expected.  My husband enjoyed his scallops although there were only 5 medium scallops on top of his risotto.  Tasty. My filet was cooked as I ordered but was barely warm.  One tiny lobster claw topped the steak which sat on top of what looked like brown potatoes.  It would have been better to have the potatoe on the side.  When ordering, I asked for a side of pasta which I was told was not available.  Emma's is basically Italian yet did not provide any Italian dishes that we go there to enjoy.  Service was less than acceptable as I our forks were taken with the salads and I had to get up and take silverware off anther table.  Bread arrived at the table next to us with their appetizer, yet we had to ask for bread after we finished our appetizer and after getting our salads.  Not Emma's typical service.  Also disappointing was that we were not given all the sauce for the calamari we brought home.  At $15 for the appetizer,  the remainder of the sauce should have been included...  Not a tiny plastic tarter sauce cup.  New Years Eve dinner was not a hit wth us this year.  We will return to Emma's but not for any future holiday dinners.
